results.name: Number of partitions into two parts which have different prime signatures.
comment: The 'prime signature' of n is the sorted list of exponents in the prime factorization of n.
Does lim n->infinity a(n)/n exist? If not, what are the limsup and liminf of a(n)/n?
results.author: _Amarnath Murthy_, Nov 11 2002
